author: woonsan
msg: JS2-949: Adds head elements contributed by the portlet fragment in portlet aggregator.
Now portlet aggregator will write <JS_PORTLET_HEAD_ELEMENTS>...</JS_PORTLET_HEAD_ELEMENTS> just before the portlet content html markup fragments.
So, desktop client splits out from the retrived content.
Because the current desktop javascript solution does not parse the retrieved html fragment, I would not wrap the result content as a xhtml dom document.
By adding some head tag fragments, it will reduce affections on performance or functionality.
